<span style="font-weight: 400;">According to World Health Organization, ‚ÄúApproximately 3% of the world population suffers from Bradycardia.‚Äù</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">¬†Bradycardia can result in serious complications if the heart fails to pump blood with enough oxygen to the body. For some people, bradycardia poses no complications.</span>

<b>However, a typical condition of Bradycardia can cause:</b>
<ul>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Fainting</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Fatigue</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Dizziness</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Shortness of breath</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Short memory</span></li>
